!More abstract archiphonemes

 * %^RC:0		 = root cons., lengthened by ^CLEN - máán%RCu máánnun
 * %^RD:0		 = root dipht., shortened by by ^RVSH - vuá%^RDg'gu vuáˊguttáá
 * %^RV:0	 	 = root vowel, lengthened by ^RLEN - ta%^RVvlu taavlu and ^RV:ˊ when WG and suffix: 0 | t | i
 * %^SC:0       = stem cons, %^SC:j, pluss lengthen after earlier shortening by %^CSH, see lyeme
 * %^SV:0 		 = stem vowel, lengthened by ^SLEN u:uu - táálu%^SV tááloost

!Triggers

 * %^CLEN:0	 = cons lengthening, with ^RC
 * %^CSH:0      = cons shortening, laaŋkku - laaŋkun
 * %^DLEN:0     = Diphtong lengthening (remove?)
 * %^RVSH:0      = Diphtong shortening
 * %^EE:0       = Final vowel deletion in ee stems (not in use)
 * %^FCD:0      = Final consonant deletion 
 * %^IA:0       = i to á (more) (not in use)
 * %^EA:0      = e to a/á in ill etc
 * %^LLEN:0     = low vow lengthening (not in use)
 * %^MONO:0     = monophtongization of diphthongs  (not in use)
 * %^RLEN:0     = root lengthening, with ^RD
 * %^RVSH:0     = root vow shortening - máán7%^RCu máˊnuttáá 
 * %^SLEN:0     = stem vowel lengthening
 * %^SFV:0      = Deleting fleeting vowel before suffix
 * %^SVLOW:0    = stem vowel lowering â>á and u>o - árppu árppoin
 * %^UU:0       = Final vowel deletion in uu stems
 * %^VLOW:0     = Vowel lowering in 3rd sg of contract verbs tuhhid:tohhe
 * %^WG:0       = weak grade trigger
 * %^ÁE:0       = á to e (more) in 3-syll
 * %^ÁI:0       = á to i (more) in 3-syll

 * %^ODRVSHV:0      =  Cns shortening in C|# and shortvow in Inf etc  (not in use)
 * %^ODDC:0        =  shorten cns in odd-syll stems before C, #  (not in use)

